rmans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1354684,"age":20,"year":"1200","julianDay":2159351,"description":"The Christian territory controlled the Kingdoms of Aragon, Navarre, and Castile.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When William Spineto was born about 1180, in Warwickshire, England, his father, Robert De Kingwarton, was 18 and his mother, Joan de Aston-Bruley, was 16. He married Joan Cocton in 1182, in Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1200, in Spain, at the age of 21."},"et":{"about 1180–1200":"umbes 1180–1200","1180–1200":"1180–1200","1189–1215":"1189–1215","1162–Female":"1162–Surnud","1188–1240":"1188–1240","1163–1199":"1163–1199","1165–1199":"1165–1199","about 1180":"umbes 1180","1165":"1165","1163":"1163","1240":"1240","1162":"1162","1182":"1182","1180":"1180","1215":"1215","1200":"1200","1189":"1189","1188":"1188","1199":"1199","11 September 1199":"11. september 1199","Coughton, Warwickshire, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Aston Bruley, Worcestershire, England":"Aston Magna, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", Warwickshire, , England":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England","Rouen, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, France":"Rouen, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Spain":"Hispaania"},"fi":{"about 1180–1200":"noin 1180–1200","1180–1200":"1180–1200","1189–1215":"1189–1215","1162–Female":"1162–Kuollut","11